description: This subseries comprises the materials originally collected by Szeemann in large envelopes in the Work in Progress room of the Fabbrica, and constitutes the core and largest part of the series. Szeemann made a folder for every name entity, even if it was just one exhibition announcement. Many of the curator files contain only a few items. There is relevant overlapping between this series and Series II. Artists. If a folder with the same name already existed in the Artist files, materials have been moved there, and these items are indicated as such on the folders. Folders related to family members who were not professionally related to the curator, such as Julie Szeemann-Kambly, have been moved to Series IX. Personal papers, and the original location of the files is indicated on the folder. Unfiled materials were found in stacks of unrelated papers on desk tops or the floor. These materials have been sorted and designated by the archivist, and moved to the Curator files if directly related to a curator already in this subseries. Mail addressed to Szeemann continued arriving after his death, and some of this mail was received as part of the archive and is found in the Unfiled folders.
